1
00:00:01,280 --> 00:00:02,960
DOCTOR: A monastery, 13th century.

2
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:04,720
Oh, we've gone all medieval.

3
00:00:04,960 --> 00:00:07,160
They're pumping something nasty
off this island.

4
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:09,720
-Ah! Ow!
-They're pumping acid off this island.

5
00:00:09,800 --> 00:00:12,800
DOCTOR: You're a factory.
A 22nd century, Army-owned factory.

6
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:15,160
CLEAVES: We're contractors
and you're trespassers.

7
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:16,760
DOCTOR: I need to see
your critical systems.

8
00:00:16,840 --> 00:00:17,840
Which one?

9
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:18,920
You know which one.

10
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,960
CLEAVES: The Flesh.
It's fully programmable matter.

11
00:00:22,040 --> 00:00:23,800
It's alive, so alive.
You're piling your lives,

12
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:25,760
your personalities directly into it.

13
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:27,880
(SCREAMING)

14
00:00:30,840 --> 00:00:34,160
DOCTOR: You gave them your lives.
Human lives are amazing.

15
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:36,280
Are you surprised
they walked off with them?

16
00:00:36,480 --> 00:00:37,480
This is...

17
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:39,000
You're telling me.

18
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:40,400
Why are you really here?

19
00:00:40,480 --> 00:00:42,320
CLEAVES: They're monsters. Mistakes.

20
00:00:42,680 --> 00:00:44,720
They have to be destroyed.

21
00:00:45,320 --> 00:00:48,920
If we want to live,
then it's time to go to war.

22
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,440
DOCTOR: They're coming back.
In a big way.

23
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:55,600
Yes, it's insane. And it's about to get
even more insanerer.

24
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:57,080
Trust me.

25
00:00:58,680 --> 00:01:00,200
I'm the Doctor.

26
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:05,640
(SCREAMING)

27
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:07,920
What's happening?

28
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:12,720
One day we will get back? Yes, one day.

29
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:16,960
Reverse the polarity
of the neutron flow.

30
00:01:17,040 --> 00:01:19,480
The Flesh is struggling to cope
with our past regenerations. Hold on!

31
00:01:22,360 --> 00:01:23,880
(FOURTH DOCTOR'S VOICE)
Would you like a jelly baby?

32
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,080
DOCTOR: Why? Why?

33
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:29,200
-Why?
-Why? Why? What?

34
00:01:29,720 --> 00:01:31,200
(TENTH DOCTOR'S VOICE)
Hello, I'm the Doctor.

35
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:33,680
No, let it go. If we've moved on...

36
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:35,960
Hold on, hold on! You can stabilise.

37
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:38,760
I've reversed the jelly baby
with the neutron flow.

38
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:40,560
And now, would you like a...

39
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:42,920
-Doctor, Doctor...
-No!

40
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:45,880
I'm the... I'm the...

41
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:50,440
-I can't...
-No, listen, hold on, hold on.

42
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:52,680
Nooo!

43
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:57,200
(SCREAMING)

44
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,760
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

45
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:35,880
(GANGERS BANGING ON DOOR)

46
00:02:42,760 --> 00:02:44,040
(BANGING STOPS)

47
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:47,440
I think I liked it best
when they were being noisy.

48
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,640
Mmm-hmm.

49
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:56,880
Doctor, we need you, get over here.

50
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,680
Hello.

51
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:01,080
-Doctor.
-Cybermats.

52
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:02,760
-Do we have time for this?
-We make time.

53
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:05,240
-I'd like more proof that you're me.
-Cybermats.

54
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:07,760
Created by the Cybermen.
They kill by feeding off brain waves.

55
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,840
Are you sure there aren't any weapons
they could get to,

56
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:11,280
like big guns with bits on?

57
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,800
Yeah, big guns would be good right now.

58
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:16,240
Why would we have guns?
We're a factory, we mine...

59
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:22,240
Acid.

60
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,000
(BANGING ON DOOR)

61
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:30,360
Rory and Amy,
they may not trust both of us.

62
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:32,440
-Are you thinking what I'm thinking?
-Inevitably.

63
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:35,000
-You see, I'm glad we're on the same...
-Wavelength. See? Great minds.

64
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:36,840
Exactly. So, what's the plan?

65
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:39,440
-Save them all, humans and Gangers.
-Tall order, sounds wonderful.

66
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:42,160
-Is that what you were thinking?
-Yes, it's just so inspiring

67
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,360
to hear me say it.

68
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:45,520
-I know.
-AMY: Doctor, come on!

69
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:50,560
-So, what now, Doctor?
-Well, time to get cracking, Doctor.

70
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:54,360
BOTH: Hello! Sorry.

71
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:57,400
-But we had to establish a few...
-Ground rules. Formulate a...

72
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:59,400
-Protocol.
-Protocol. Very posh.

73
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:01,160
No, no. A protocol between us,
otherwise...

74
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:03,760
-It gets horribly embarrassing.
-Potentially confusing.

75
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:06,320
Okay. Well, I'm glad you solved
the problem of confusing.

76
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:09,880
-That's sarcasm.
-She's very good at sarcasm.

77
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,040
-BOTH: Breathe.
-What?

78
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,800
-We have to get you outside.
-And the Gangers, too.

79
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:14,720
Sorry. Would you like a memo
from the last meeting?

80
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,560
-They are trying to kill us!
-They're scared.

81
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:18,120
Doctor, we're trapped in here.

82
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:20,320
Right. See, I don't think so.

83
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:23,040
The Flesh Bowl is filled by cabling
from above.

84
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:24,760
But where are
the earthing conduits, hmm?

85
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:28,880
All this piping must go down
into a tunnel or a shaft or something.

86
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:30,600
Yes? With us?

87
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:35,560
Yowza! An escape route.

88
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:38,520
You know, I'm just starting to get
a sense of just how impressive it is

89
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:40,000
to hang out with me.

90
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:43,400
-Do you tend to say "yowza"?
-That's enough. Let it go, okay?

91
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:45,600
We're under stress.

92
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,680
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

93
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,600
(RASPING)

94
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:14,600
Stop. Stop. Stop. Stop.

95
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:17,120
(LIQUID DRIPPING)

96
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,360
The Army will send a recon team out.

97
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:47,040
We need to find a way
to contact the mainland.

98
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:48,720
What about Rory and Jen?
They are both out there.

99
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,960
No, this place is a maze.

100
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,400
Takes a long time 10 find someone
in a maze.

101
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:53,360
I bet you lot have got
a computer map, haven't you?

102
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:55,800
If we can get power running and
scan for them, it'll be a lot quicker.

103
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:56,880
(COUGHING)

104
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,920
Doctor, you said earlier to breathe.

105
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,360
Very important, Pond, breathe.

106
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:04,120
Yeah, well, I'm struggling to.

107
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:05,240
(ALL COUGHING)

108
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:09,360
Acid interacting with the stone.

109
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:11,480
Creating an asphyxiant miasma.

110
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:14,240
-A what?
-Chokey gas.

111
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:16,440
Extra heavy. If we can get above it...

112
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:18,400
The evac tower. This way!

113
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:25,120
(GROANS) Damned headaches.

114
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:27,680
So tired.

115
00:06:27,960 --> 00:06:30,280
They could be anywhere.

116
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:33,240
-How are we going to find them?
-Think about it.

117
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:35,880
With all that gas out there,
my guess would be the evac tower.

118
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:37,840
Get above it, try to get power up.

119
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:40,640
So, let's stop them.

120
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:43,800
It's a narrow doorway.
I could defend it easy enough.

121
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:45,720
So can she. (CHUCKLES)

122
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,560
(GROANS)

123
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:51,120
(COUGHING)

124
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,400
(GROANING)

125
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,720
I think I've coughed so hard
I've pulled a muscle or something.

126
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:58,240
It's okay. It's easing off. Whoo! Okay.

127
00:06:58,840 --> 00:06:59,840
(BELL TOLLING)

128
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,200
Midnight.

129
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,840
It's Adam's birthday.

130
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:06,440
My son's five.

131
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:09,520
Happy birthday, bud.

132
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:15,800
Happy birthday, Adam.

133
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:23,520
He'll be so excited.

134
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:26,320
Out of bed at the crack of dawn.

135
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,480
(CHUCKLING) It's funny.

136
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:32,440
He's got this wee dance he does
when he gets over-excited.

137
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:33,560
(DOOR OPENING)

138
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:36,960
Listen to me.
I tried to block the memories,

139
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:39,480
but now I know, I must remember.

140
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:43,880
It's the eyes.
The eyes are the last to go.

141
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,600
What are you talking about?

142
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:49,200
When they destroy us,
the eyes are the last things to melt.

143
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:52,000
And there's one question in those eyes.

144
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:53,080
Why?

145
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:58,240
Why should we suffer
for the sake of human beings?

146
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,360
I heard in India there's over
10 million Gangers.

147
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:04,400
We can reach out.

148
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:06,960
Inspire them to rise up.

149
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:11,040
Revolution? Look, I just...

150
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:14,040
I just want to be left
to live in peace, Jen.

151
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:18,040
They will melt you.

152
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:22,040
Have you become so human
that you've forgotten the truth?

153
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:25,040
Don't you remember all the times
you were decommissioned?

154
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:27,360
-Or should I say executed?
-No.

155
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,320
We don't remember.

156
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:31,880
Well, I do.

157
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:35,280
It's us or them.

158
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,680
She's right.

159
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:03,960
JENNIFER: I have a plan.

160
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:08,720
And it'll destroy them all.

161
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:14,200
Can you really get the power back?

162
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:16,240
There's always some power
floating around...

163
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,440
Sticking to the wires like bits of lint.

164
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:21,240
-Can you stop finishing each other's...
-Sentences?

165
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,720
-No probs.
-Yes.

166
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:27,280
No, but hang on. You said that
the Tardis was stuck in acid.

167
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:28,400
So won't she be damaged?

168
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:30,200
-Nah...
-She's a tough old thing.

169
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:33,160
Tough, old, sexy.

170
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:35,640
No, tough, dependable, sexy.

171
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:37,240
-I can't get it out of there.
-Come on.

172
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:39,680
Okay, how can you both be real?

173
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:43,200
Well, because we are. I'm the Doctor.

174
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:45,160
Yeah, and so am I.
We both contain the knowledge

175
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,880
of over 900 years of
memory and experience.

176
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:48,720
We both wear the same bow tie,
which is cool.

177
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:50,440
-Because bow ties are...
-And always will be.

178
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:53,360
But how did the Flesh read you?
Because you weren't linked up to it.

179
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,920
Well, it must have been
after I examined it.

180
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,600
-Thus a new, genuine Doctor was created.
-Ta-da!

181
00:09:57,960 --> 00:10:00,640
No getting away from it.
One of you was here first.

182
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:04,160
Well, okay, after the Flesh scanned me,
I had an accident with a puddle of acid.

183
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:05,560
Now new shoes,

184
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:08,600
a situation which did not confront
me learned self here.

185
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:13,440
That satisfy you, Pond?

186
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:14,960
Don't call me Pond, please.

187
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:19,960
What?

188
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:22,560
Interesting. You definitely feel
more affection for him than me.

189
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:27,400
No. No, I... Look, you're fine
and everything, but he's the Doctor.

190
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:31,320
No offence. Being almost the Doctor
is pretty damn impressive.

191
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:34,440
Well, being almost the Doctor is like
being no Doctor at all.

192
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:35,600
Don't overreact.

193
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:37,880
-You might as well call me Smith.
-Smith?

194
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:40,760
-John Smith!
-Yes! Communication a go go.

195
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:44,120
Find Rory, show me the scanning
tracking screen.

196
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,320
(BLEEPING)

197
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:47,440
Come on, Rory, let's be having you.

198
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:48,960
CLEAVES: There's no sign of him
anywhere.

199
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:51,520
Come on, come on, baby, show yourself.

200
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,160
You're right. There's power.

201
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:57,600
Now, boys, I don't know much,
but I know my own minds.

202
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:59,680
She'll be straight on the comm link
to the mainland.

203
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:02,760
St John's calling. Emergency Alpha.

204
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,280
Let's see if we can intercept.

205
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:07,600
St John's calling the mainland.
Are you receiving me, Captain?

206
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:09,080
Come in.

207
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:13,360
We'll never get a signal
through this storm.

208
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:17,240
St John's calling the mainland.

209
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:19,840
Come in, this is urgent.

210
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:22,040
CAPTAIN: We're just about
reading you, St John's.

211
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:23,160
How are you doing?

212
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:24,640
We've had all kinds of trouble here.

213
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:27,640
CLEAVES: Request immediate evacuation.
We're under attack.

214
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:30,440
The storm's affected our Gangers.
They're running amok.

215
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:33,400
-CAPTAIN: Your Gangers?
-Yes, our Gangers are attacking us.

216
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:35,880
We need you to take us
off the island immediately

217
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:37,520
and wipe them out.

218
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:45,320
Copy that, St John's.
Shuttle's dispatched. Hang on.

219
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:48,840
You'll need to airlift us off the roof
of the evac tower.

220
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:51,760
And, Captain, any further transmission
sent by me

221
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:55,000
must come with the following code word,
I'm typing it

222
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:57,200
in case they're listening in.

223
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:59,280
Qof, see how smart I am?

224
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,800
That's why I'm paid the big bucks.

225
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:05,080
CAPTAIN: Got it. We'll swing in,
get you out and decommission the Flesh.

226
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:12,120
Jennifer's right.

227
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:15,280
We're going to have to fight
if we want to survive.

228
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:17,600
(PANTING)

229
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,880
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Thermostatic override rejected.

230
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:29,120
Can only be operated
by a recognised source.

231
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,400
I am recognised.

232
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,400
I'm Jennifer Lucas.

233
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:37,000
Oh!

234
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:39,880
We're going to get out of here.
We are, we're going to get out.

235
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:41,320
But we're not leaving without them.

236
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:43,480
I want him found, too,
but it's about casualties, isn't it?

237
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:44,560
Can't be helped.

238
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,120
(MACHINE BEEPING)

239
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:47,480
What are you doing?

240
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:48,600
-Making a phone call.
-Who to?

241
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:49,800
No one yet. It's on delay.

242
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:52,760
Right. Not getting it.
Why exactly are you making a phone call?

243
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:55,920
Because, Amy, I am
and always will be the optimist.

244
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:59,680
The ho per of far-flung hopes
and dreamer of improbable dreams.

245
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:00,920
(YELPS)

246
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:04,400
Wheels are in motion. Done.

247
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:10,200
Do you know, really,
there could be only one.

248
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:12,960
-Hmm?
-Ah, nothing. Carry on.

249
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:14,400
Be amazing.

250
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:25,800
(GASPS)

251
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:37,040
(GASPS)

252
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:43,840
Amy, what happened?

253
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,720
-It's her again.
-It's who again?

254
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:54,200
There's a woman I keep seeing,
a woman with an eye patch.

255
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:57,880
And she has this habit of sliding
walls open and staring at me.

256
00:13:58,680 --> 00:14:00,040
-Doctor?
-Nothing.

257
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:01,480
Doesn't seem like nothing.

258
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:03,480
It's time memory, like a mirage.

259
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:05,240
It's nothing to worry about.

260
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:06,880
It's in my head.

261
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:12,480
-Hey, hold on.
-Don't go!

262
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,240
No, leave it to me.

263
00:14:30,280 --> 00:14:31,640
I'm sorry.

264
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:35,760
What I said about you being
almost the Doctor, it's just...

265
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:40,280
It's just really hard because
I've been through so much with him.

266
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:42,200
I've even seen...

267
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:45,880
I've even seen the moment of his...

268
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:48,800
Can you die?

269
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:51,720
If you really are the same,
then you can die,

270
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:54,000
you can be killed and...

271
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,200
I might have seen that happen.

272
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:03,640
-Why?
-Why?

273
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:05,640
Because you invited us to see it.

274
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:07,440
Your death... (YELPS)

275
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:11,040
-Why?
-You're hurting me.

276
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:13,240
It's all the eyes say. Why?

277
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,760
I can feel them.

278
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:18,040
As they work each day, knowing the time
was coming for them

279
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:19,400
to be thrown away again!

280
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:21,840
Not again! Please!

281
00:15:21,920 --> 00:15:24,080
And then they are destroyed
and they feel death.

282
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:26,840
And all they can say is, "Why?"

283
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:42,080
Why?

284
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:45,720
Keep him away from me!

285
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:48,360
Did you sense it?

286
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:50,120
Briefly, not as strong as you.

287
00:15:51,480 --> 00:15:52,800
Amy, I'm sorry.

288
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:55,200
No! Hey, you keep away.
We can't trust you.

289
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:57,760
It would appear
I can connect to the Flesh.

290
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:58,840
No, you are Flesh.

291
00:15:58,920 --> 00:16:00,200
I'm beginning to understand what
he's been through,

292
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:02,120
-what he needs.
-What you want. You are it!

293
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:05,160
It's much more powerful than we thought.
The Flesh can grow, correct?

294
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:07,040
Its cells can divide.

295
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:13,440
Well, now it wants to do that at will.

296
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:15,000
It wants revenge.

297
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:17,640
It's in pain, angry.

298
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,760
It wants revenge.

299
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:22,320
I was right, you're not the Doctor,
you can't ever be.

300
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:25,080
-You're just a copy.
-Doctor?

301
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:28,760
It might be best if you stayed
over there for now. Hmm?

302
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:30,240
Hold on a minute. Hold your horses.

303
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:32,240
I thought I'd explained this,
I'm him, he's me.

304
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:35,200
Doctor, we have no issue with you.

305
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:36,960
But when it comes to your Ganger...

306
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:39,240
DOCTOR: Don't be so absurd.

307
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:41,240
-Buzzer.
-Sure, boss.

308
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:49,640
Take a seat, mate.

309
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:52,280
Nice barrel, very comfy.

310
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:53,800
Why not?

311
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:55,880
Is this really what you want?

312
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:07,440
JENNIFER: Help me! No! Get away!

313
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:08,600
Jen?

314
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:12,240
Jen!

315
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:16,400
Rory?

316
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,320
I'm sorry, she found me.

317
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:23,160
-Rory, listen to me.
-Don't listen to her.

318
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:26,000
I'm Jennifer Lucas, this woman is Flesh.

319
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:32,840
CAPTAIN: This is the shuttle.
We're right above you.

320
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:34,160
But we can't get low enough.

321
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:36,320
Gamma static could fry our nav controls.

322
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:38,440
Sit tight, we'll get you. Just...

323
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:39,920
(BLEEPING)

324
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:43,360
Hello? Can you hear me?

325
00:17:43,640 --> 00:17:45,320
I can't find Rory. I'm going out there.

326
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:46,600
We could use the sonic to track him.

327
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:48,960
Humans and Gangers give off
slightly different signals,

328
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:50,480
the sonic needs to tell the difference.

329
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:52,520
Oh, so the sonic knows
Gangers are different.

330
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,760
-So the other Doctor is different.
-He is the Doctor.

331
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:56,680
Not to me, I can tell.

332
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,280
Sure you're not prejudiced?

333
00:17:58,360 --> 00:17:59,480
Nice try. But I know, okay?

334
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:01,960
We've been through too much.
You're my Doctor, end of.

335
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,480
So, one of you is human.

336
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:06,400
And one of you
I sat with and talked with.

337
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:08,440
Why can't you just tell me the truth?

338
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:12,000
The Doctor wants you to live
and I'm with him all the way.

339
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:14,560
That's a lovely idea, Rory.

340
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:17,720
But the Flesh want to kill us now.

341
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:20,480
You're limping. You're not.

342
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:22,560
So?

343
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:24,480
So what? You think a Ganger
can't put on a limp?

344
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:26,080
Show me your leg.

345
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:29,960
It got burnt while I was in the harness.

346
00:18:30,040 --> 00:18:32,640
She's lying.
She's telling you what you want to hear.

347
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:34,240
Look, you can't fake a burn.

348
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:36,360
No! No! You don't...

349
00:18:36,880 --> 00:18:38,560
(BOTH GRUNTING)

350
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:41,760
RORY: Stop it! Stop it!

351
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:43,920
Fighting each other is pointless.
Come on!

352
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:46,920
Please, please, stop!

353
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:51,600
Jen! Both Jens, stop it!

354
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,360
(SCREAMING)

355
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:54,640
No!

356
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:56,640
(ACID HISSING)

357
00:18:58,840 --> 00:18:59,840
(GRUNTING)

358
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:03,160
She attacked me. I didn't...

359
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:12,160
I knew you'd find me.

360
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:16,160
We're in this together, Rory.
And we've got to trust each other.

361
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:20,760
Okay. Come on, let's go.

362
00:19:26,480 --> 00:19:28,840
Hey, there's a camera up.
We've got a visual.

363
00:19:31,040 --> 00:19:32,040
AMY: That's Rory and Jennifer.

364
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:35,400
They're heading
for the thermostatic room.

365
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:36,800
Let's go get them.

366
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,000
Hang on.

367
00:19:41,320 --> 00:19:43,160
CLEAVES: You can't let him go.
Are you crazy?

368
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:45,760
Am I crazy, Doctor?

369
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:48,480
Well, you did once plumb your brain
into the core of an entire planet

370
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:50,640
just to hold its orbit and win a bet.

371
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:52,640
He can't go rescue them. I'm going.

372
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:55,360
Do you know, I want him to go.

373
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,560
And I'm rather adamant.

374
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:09,480
Well, then, they'll need company.
Right, boss?

375
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,120
It's fine. I'll handle it.

376
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:14,720
Thank you, Buzzer.

377
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,160
It'll be all right.

378
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:17,840
I'll find him.

379
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:23,120
DOCTOR: Can't explain it to you now,
but I need you to trust him.

380
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:24,840
Can you do that for me, Amy?

381
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:26,360
And what if you're wrong?

382
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:30,400
(BOTH COUGHING)

383
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:34,480
This is the thermostatic chamber.
We can stir the oxygen supply from here.

384
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:35,560
Uh, what?

385
00:20:36,280 --> 00:20:38,800
We're going to choke to death
if we don't clean this air.

386
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:40,800
Keep a look out in case of Gangers.

387
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:44,440
(COUGHING)

388
00:20:48,120 --> 00:20:49,680
JENNIFER: Rory!

389
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:51,960
What's wrong?

390
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:55,200
It's this wheel, it's just too tough
for a girl to turn.

391
00:20:55,280 --> 00:20:57,000
You feeling strong?

392
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:59,320
I'll break out the big guns.

393
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:00,880
This first.

394
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:07,400
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Human source recognised.

395
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:15,680
Thermostatic override granted.

396
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:20,080
These temperature gauges are rising.

397
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:23,560
Jennifer and Rory must've shut off
the underground cooling vents.

398
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:25,120
Why do that? It'll kill us.

399
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:27,880
There's a million gallons
of boiling acid under our feet.

400
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:29,160
I know, it's heating up
the whole island.

401
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:31,280
How long until it blows?

402
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:33,120
(LOUD RUMBLING)

403
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:36,840
Gangers or no Gangers,
we need to get the hell out of here.

404
00:21:37,080 --> 00:21:38,680
Shuttle, we need evac.

405
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,840
Where are you? Can you hear me?

406
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:42,560
-Can you...
-Cleaves?

407
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:45,000
-Cleaves? Cleaves, sit down.
-I'm fine.

408
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:50,920
You don't look good.

409
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,720
Monsters never do.

410
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:55,160
I'm fine.

411
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:57,440
I remember medics doing tests.

412
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:59,320
I'm waiting for results, so let it go.

413
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:01,640
It's a very deep parietal clot.

414
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:03,120
How can you possibly...

415
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:06,120
(SIGHS)

416
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:07,760
Inoperable?

417
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:08,920
On Earth, yes.

418
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,800
Well, seeing as Earth's all that's on...

419
00:22:12,880 --> 00:22:15,680
...offer. Hmm. (CHUCKLES)

420
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:19,440
I'm no healthy spring chicken
and you're no weatherman, right?

421
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:21,040
(RUMBLING)

422
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:23,440
Something just cracked, I heard it.

423
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:24,840
Yeah, we can't stay here. Let's go!

424
00:22:24,920 --> 00:22:27,360
-He's right, let's shift!
-Cleaves to shuttle, respond.

425
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:30,120
We need to move and we can't be
collected from the evac tower.

426
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:32,360
-CAPTAIN: Give us the code word.
-The code word is...

427
00:22:32,440 --> 00:22:33,840
(EXPLODING)

428
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:35,280
(ALL GRUNTING)

429
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:36,360
(ALARM SOUNDING)

430
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:40,080
Cleaves, Cleaves, it's dead! It's dead.
We need to get out of here.

431
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:42,640
We need to get back downstairs
and get those vents back on! Come on!

432
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:47,120
This is our chance. How can we route
the shuttle to the courtyard?

433
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,560
You can't guess the code word.

434
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:50,920
Yes, I can, Jimmy,
because I created the code word.

435
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,480
Shuttle, do you read me?
This is Foreman Cleaves.

436
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:58,000
Cleaves, you... You got cut off.
Say again. What's the request?

437
00:22:58,080 --> 00:22:59,920
You need to reroute and pick us up
from the courtyard.

438
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:01,040
Courtyard?

439
00:23:01,240 --> 00:23:03,520
As soon as we can.
Give me the code word.

440
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:05,920
Shuttle, the code word is Bad Boy.

441
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:08,040
I repeat, Bad Boy.

442
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:14,520
Copy that. The courtyard.

443
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:16,520
Still want us
to take care of those Gangers?

444
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:19,400
Negative. They've all been incinerated.

445
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:21,880
Bad Boy.

446
00:23:22,080 --> 00:23:23,080
Good call.

447
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:26,120
Yeah, well, it wasn't luck.

448
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:28,040
We're the same person.

449
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:35,480
This room's always sealed.

450
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:38,160
Power surge must've thrown the bolts.

451
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:44,360
What is that?

452
00:23:48,040 --> 00:23:50,880
Discarded Flesh. Faulty, probably.

453
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:53,240
Just thrown away. Look at them.

454
00:23:58,040 --> 00:23:59,440
One of my old Gangers.

455
00:23:59,920 --> 00:24:01,600
(YELPS)

456
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:05,480
Left to rot, fully conscious.

457
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:08,640
Can you imagine
what kind of hell they're in?

458
00:24:08,960 --> 00:24:12,840
But Cleaves... (STAMMERING)
The company, how could they do this?

459
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:14,720
How could they?

460
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:16,760
Who are the real monsters?

461
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:21,880
We can't let this carry on.

462
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:24,760
Jen, we have to make people see.

463
00:24:26,760 --> 00:24:29,040
Okay, Rory, I have an idea.

464
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:31,880
You came for me. We have a bond, right?

465
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:33,800
We trust each other.

466
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:37,200
-Yeah.
-So, trust me on this.

467
00:24:41,440 --> 00:24:42,720
I'm getting something.

468
00:24:42,800 --> 00:24:43,960
-Is it human?
-Yeah, it's human.

469
00:24:44,040 --> 00:24:47,240
But it's fading, it's fading!
This is bad. Fading is very...

470
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:48,920
bad.

471
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:52,360
-(GRUNTS)
-The signal's gone.

472
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:53,480
She's dead.

473
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:55,880
(SIGHING) She was hanging to
the edge of life

474
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:58,760
but she just, just slipped away.

475
00:24:59,360 --> 00:25:01,840
(SIGHS) Jennifer, I'm so sorry.

476
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:06,240
Oh, she's been out here for hours.

477
00:25:06,360 --> 00:25:09,240
But if the real Jen's been
lying out here...

478
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:11,480
Rory's in trouble.

479
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:19,840
Sorry, pal. It's boss' orders.
Us and them, innit?

480
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:27,240
Ah.

481
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:30,160
The eyes have it.

482
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:34,280
AMY: Why are they here?

483
00:25:35,240 --> 00:25:39,040
To accuse us.

484
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:41,960
Ignore them, it's not far.

485
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:54,960
(RUMBLING)

486
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:58,000
I should've been a postman like me dad.

487
00:25:58,080 --> 00:25:59,520
(JENNIFER SHUSHING)

488
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:03,880
I'm here, I'm here.

489
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:07,560
I'm with you.

490
00:26:09,440 --> 00:26:11,920
I know, it hurts.

491
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:15,880
I'm sorry.

492
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:18,520
Go to sleep.

493
00:26:19,840 --> 00:26:21,040
Sleep.

494
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:23,920
BUZZER: You killed her.

495
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:25,800
You killed our Jen.

496
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:31,120
And I'm stronger, Buzz.

497
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:36,440
I can grow.

498
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:45,960
(BUZZER SCREAMING)

499
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:50,080
(ALARMS SOUNDING)

500
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:52,800
It's a chemical chain reaction now.
I can't stop it.

501
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:56,000
This place is going to blow sky high.

502
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:57,480
Exactly how long have we got?

503
00:26:57,560 --> 00:27:00,920
An hour? Five seconds?
Somewhere in between.

504
00:27:01,160 --> 00:27:02,680
(KLAXON SOUNDING)

505
00:27:03,320 --> 00:27:04,520
Out!

506
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:09,200
RORY: Oh, all right.

507
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:11,440
-Oh, Rory, oh, Rory.
-Oh.

508
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:13,000
There's a way out, Jennifer found it.

509
00:27:13,080 --> 00:27:14,760
A secret tunnel under the crypt.

510
00:27:14,840 --> 00:27:17,000
From the crypt?
It's not on the schematics.

511
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:20,120
It leads right out of the monastery,
maybe even under the Tardis, Doctor.

512
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:21,280
Follow me.

513
00:27:25,040 --> 00:27:26,040
(KLAXON SOUNDING)

514
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:31,160
Ah.

515
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:37,640
Got anything for a sore head?

516
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:43,080
This is how they'll always treat us.
Do you see now?

517
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:46,360
After all, you're one of us,

518
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:47,440
Doctor.

519
00:27:49,120 --> 00:27:51,640
(SIGHS) Call me Smith.

520
00:27:52,720 --> 00:27:53,720
John Smith.

521
00:27:57,480 --> 00:27:59,280
We can't leave without Buzzer!

522
00:27:59,360 --> 00:28:01,040
I'll go back for him.

523
00:28:01,120 --> 00:28:04,320
Uh, Doctor, look, I'd better tell you,
I haven't been quite straight with you.

524
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:05,400
DOCTOR: Rory!

525
00:28:06,360 --> 00:28:07,760
Hang on, Jen, we don't want to
lock them out.

526
00:28:07,840 --> 00:28:09,160
We should just show them
what we've found.

527
00:28:09,240 --> 00:28:10,720
I don't think so.

528
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:14,400
-Rory Pond. Roranicus Pondicus!
-Rory, what the hell are you playing at?

529
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:19,320
They've been throwing away
old Flesh and leaving it to rot

530
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:20,400
alive!

531
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:21,960
I think the world should see that.

532
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:25,160
Rory, there is no time.
This factory's about to explode!

533
00:28:25,240 --> 00:28:26,960
Are you sure about this?

534
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:28,880
'Cause I'm not. Let them out.

535
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:32,200
-The little girl got strong.
-What?

536
00:28:32,520 --> 00:28:35,040
The little girl lost on the moors
in her red wellies,

537
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:36,800
looking for a way home.

538
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:39,680
Well, she got strong, Rory.

539
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:44,280
-I told you, remember?
-But that wasn't...

540
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:47,560
It was the other Jennifer that told me
about being a little girl.

541
00:28:47,640 --> 00:28:48,680
Oh?

542
00:28:49,840 --> 00:28:51,720
What other Jennifer?

543
00:28:53,280 --> 00:28:54,720
Well, the...

544
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:56,480
The, uh...

545
00:28:56,880 --> 00:28:59,400
Wait, you tricked me. Let me go,
I'm opening the door, let me...

546
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:00,560
I'm sorry!

547
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:03,400
No!

548
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:11,840
We have to be free.

549
00:29:12,600 --> 00:29:14,800
I'm sorry, too, Miranda.

550
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:18,240
Of all the humans in all the world,
you had to pick the one with the clot.

551
00:29:21,160 --> 00:29:25,000
But hey, them's the breaks!
Welcome to the human race.

552
00:29:33,520 --> 00:29:35,040
(SONIC BEEPING)

553
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:38,920
This is going to overheat
and fill the room with acid.

554
00:29:39,040 --> 00:29:40,160
Just as a point of interest.

555
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:43,200
-And we can't stop it?
-Just as a point of interest?

556
00:29:43,280 --> 00:29:44,880
-(LOUD THUMPING)
-No.

557
00:29:46,840 --> 00:29:50,520
You created another Ganger
just to trick me. You tricked me!

558
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:53,080
When I found you, you were both Flesh.

559
00:29:53,160 --> 00:29:56,040
And you tricked me into trusting you!

560
00:29:58,480 --> 00:29:59,920
Jen's dead.

561
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:04,000
-Isn't she?
-She's gone, Rory! Gone!

562
00:30:04,080 --> 00:30:06,680
CAPTAIN: Shuttle. We're dropping down
on our approach.

563
00:30:06,760 --> 00:30:08,600
Stand by for evac.

564
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:11,240
The humans will be melted,
as they deserve.

565
00:30:11,320 --> 00:30:13,400
And then the factory will be destroyed.

566
00:30:13,480 --> 00:30:16,480
Once we get to the mainland,
the real battle begins.

567
00:30:16,560 --> 00:30:18,640
The humans won't stand a chance.

568
00:30:18,720 --> 00:30:21,880
You're one of us, Doctor.
Join the revolution.

569
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:24,600
I've got to go and get them out!

570
00:30:33,280 --> 00:30:34,520
It'll never hold her.

571
00:30:34,600 --> 00:30:36,440
If you have a better plan, I'm all ears.

572
00:30:36,600 --> 00:30:39,120
In fact, if you have a better plan,
I'll take you to a planet

573
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:41,280
where everyone is all ears.

574
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:44,360
Doctor, we can't just let them die.

575
00:30:46,040 --> 00:30:48,120
-Ring ring.
-Doctor!

576
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:49,840
Ring ring!

577
00:30:51,760 --> 00:30:52,800
Oh...

578
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:55,560
The acid's eating through.

579
00:30:57,560 --> 00:30:58,680
(EXCLAIMS)

580
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:00,960
(CRASHING)

581
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:03,400
-Stay!
-Okay.

582
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:06,640
(PHONE RINGING)

583
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:08,240
Ah, that'll be the phone.
Somebody get the phone.

584
00:31:08,320 --> 00:31:11,480
Jimmy, get the phone.
No, fine, I'll get the phone. Stay put.

585
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:20,480
AUTOMATED VOICE: Thank you for booking
your holo-call with Morpeth Jetsan.

586
00:31:20,560 --> 00:31:23,200
Ah! Hello, madam.

587
00:31:23,320 --> 00:31:27,000
I'm the Doctor. Well, other Doctor.
Well, Smith.

588
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:30,880
It's complicated and boring.
Anyway, who cares? It's your birthday!

589
00:31:30,960 --> 00:31:32,360
-Ya y_/
-Yay!

590
00:31:32,560 --> 00:31:35,080
Now, have you been getting up
very early and jumping on the bed?

591
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:36,480
Yes, really high.

592
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:37,960
I expect chocolate for breakfast.

593
00:31:38,040 --> 00:31:40,520
If you don't feel sick by mid-morning,
you're not doing it right.

594
00:31:40,600 --> 00:31:43,640
Now, I think you want to speak to Dad.

595
00:31:43,720 --> 00:31:44,720
Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.

596
00:31:45,840 --> 00:31:46,840
Daddy?

597
00:31:49,120 --> 00:31:50,360
You'll do, Jimmy.

598
00:31:51,360 --> 00:31:54,480
What does the other Jimmy matter now?
You're both the same dad, aren't you?

599
00:31:58,040 --> 00:31:59,360
Come on. Adam's waiting.

600
00:32:01,840 --> 00:32:03,120
Daddy...

601
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:04,320
(LOUD RUMBLING)

602
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:07,840
Daddy, what's that rumbly noise?

603
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:10,160
What's going on, Daddy?

604
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:11,800
Daddy?

605
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:14,720
You tricked him into an act
of weakness, Doctor.

606
00:32:15,120 --> 00:32:18,000
No, I've helped him
into an act of humanity.

607
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:22,160
Anyone else like the sound
of that act of humanity?

608
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:25,760
Dicken, drain the acid well
in Crypt One.

609
00:32:25,840 --> 00:32:28,280
-Don't you dare!
-I've had it with this.

610
00:32:28,360 --> 00:32:31,240
What's the point in this ridiculous war?

611
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:34,000
Look at you, Jen.

612
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:37,280
You were a sweet kid. Look at you now.

613
00:32:38,120 --> 00:32:39,720
The stuff of nightmares.

614
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:44,280
I don't want my world
populated by monsters.

615
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:50,680
You can't stop the factory
from melting down, boss.

616
00:32:50,920 --> 00:32:53,560
I'll take revenge on humanity
with or without you.

617
00:32:53,640 --> 00:32:55,520
It doesn't have to be about revenge.

618
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:57,440
It can be so much better than that.

619
00:33:02,400 --> 00:33:03,520
(GRUNTING)

620
00:33:14,760 --> 00:33:15,840
(BEEPING)

621
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:21,080
(SCREAMING)

622
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:25,320
Let me through!

623
00:33:29,800 --> 00:33:32,440
There's nothing we can do.
The acid's reached his heart.

624
00:33:33,640 --> 00:33:34,680
(GASPING)

625
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:38,480
-Hang in there, mate.
-I'm quite handsome from this angle.

626
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:41,480
(GASPING)

627
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:45,520
I'm sorry.

628
00:33:47,080 --> 00:33:48,240
I'm the fake.

629
00:33:50,080 --> 00:33:52,160
Adam deserves his real dad.

630
00:33:52,320 --> 00:33:55,080
-Shut up.
-What do you want me to do?

631
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:57,440
Anything.

632
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:00,000
Just say.

633
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:03,320
The way things are, mate,

634
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:06,720
it's up to you now.

635
00:34:17,120 --> 00:34:18,280
Be a dad.

636
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:23,160
You remember how.

637
00:34:35,680 --> 00:34:39,880
Jimmy Wicks, you're a dad.

638
00:34:54,200 --> 00:34:57,920
Daddy? Where's my daddy?

639
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:22,520
Daddy, it's me.

640
00:35:24,560 --> 00:35:28,280
(CHUCKLES) Hey, sunshine.

641
00:35:29,080 --> 00:35:30,280
What are you up to?

642
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:32,240
Opening all my presents.

643
00:35:32,440 --> 00:35:34,160
Ah, good lad.

644
00:35:34,240 --> 00:35:35,960
You have fun today.

645
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:41,440
And remember your dad,
he loves you very, very much.

646
00:35:41,920 --> 00:35:43,680
When are you coming home?

647
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:48,880
-Daddy's coming home today, Adam.
-Yay!

648
00:35:54,480 --> 00:35:55,600
Now we need to move.

649
00:35:55,880 --> 00:35:57,160
(PANTING)

650
00:35:59,800 --> 00:36:00,880
(DOOR OPENING)

651
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:03,880
(ALARM SOUNDING)

652
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:05,400
(SNARLING)

653
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:11,000
Run. Run!

654
00:36:12,080 --> 00:36:13,240
Run!

655
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:20,840
(RUMBLING)

656
00:36:20,920 --> 00:36:22,760
Ooh, roof's going to give.

657
00:36:24,240 --> 00:36:26,960
We have to stop her!
This door doesn't lock!

658
00:36:27,040 --> 00:36:29,040
No, but the far one does.

659
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:37,520
(SNARLING)

660
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:57,480
-(SCREAMING)
-No!

661
00:37:00,520 --> 00:37:01,960
Here she comes.

662
00:37:06,680 --> 00:37:07,840
Whoa!

663
00:37:08,920 --> 00:37:11,560
Oh! She does like to make an entrance!

664
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:15,320
Get on the move!

665
00:37:16,880 --> 00:37:19,760
-Go, go, go!
-Get aboard! Go!

666
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:20,840
I'm not leaving.

667
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:23,840
(EXCLAIMS)

668
00:37:24,240 --> 00:37:25,320
Go!

669
00:37:31,600 --> 00:37:33,400
Hey, hey. Now's our chance.

670
00:37:33,480 --> 00:37:35,760
I have to stay, hold this door closed.
Give you time to dematerialise.

671
00:37:35,840 --> 00:37:37,920
Oh, don't be crazy.
Okay, what happens to you, hmm?

672
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:40,160
Well, this place
is just about to explode.

673
00:37:40,240 --> 00:37:41,400
But I can stop her.

674
00:37:41,640 --> 00:37:43,680
Both of you can survive this.
I mean, there has to be a way.

675
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:47,120
Or perhaps you think
I should stay instead, Mr Smith?

676
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:50,480
No, of course not.

677
00:37:50,680 --> 00:37:52,320
But look, this man, I've flown with him.

678
00:37:52,640 --> 00:37:55,320
You know? And you are amazing,
and yeah, I misjudged you.

679
00:37:55,400 --> 00:37:57,840
But you're not him, I'm sorry.

680
00:38:00,080 --> 00:38:01,680
Amy, we swapped shoes.

681
00:38:02,480 --> 00:38:05,120
-I'm the Doctor.
-And I'm the Flesh.

682
00:38:05,840 --> 00:38:07,720
You can't be. You're the real him.

683
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:09,760
No, I'm not
and I haven't been all along.

684
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:12,080
-What?
-I'm the original Doctor, Amy.

685
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:13,680
We had to know
if we were truly the same.

686
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:15,800
It was important, vital we learn
about the Flesh.

687
00:38:15,880 --> 00:38:18,800
And we could only do that
through your eyes.

688
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:31,400
I never thought it possible.

689
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:33,000
What?

690
00:38:33,920 --> 00:38:36,720
You're twice the man I thought you were.

691
00:38:41,480 --> 00:38:42,720
DOCTOR: Push, Amy.

692
00:38:43,960 --> 00:38:46,320
But only when she tells you to.

693
00:38:48,600 --> 00:38:49,600
Amy, come on!

694
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:53,720
(LOUD SNARLING)

695
00:38:54,560 --> 00:38:56,120
Well, my death arrives, I suppose.

696
00:38:56,200 --> 00:38:58,360
-But this one we're not invited to.
-Pardon?

697
00:38:58,440 --> 00:39:01,320
Nothing. Your molecular memory
can survive this, you know,

698
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:03,800
it may not be the end.

699
00:39:05,120 --> 00:39:06,680
Well, if I turn up to nick
all your biscuits,

700
00:39:06,760 --> 00:39:07,880
then you'll know you were right,
won't you?

701
00:39:12,640 --> 00:39:15,080
Doctor! No, please...

702
00:39:15,840 --> 00:39:17,120
(BANGING)

703
00:39:17,800 --> 00:39:20,000
-You too, Cleaves, off you pop.
-I'm staying here.

704
00:39:20,200 --> 00:39:21,440
This is not the time for grand gestures.

705
00:39:21,520 --> 00:39:22,680
Says the king of grand gestures.

706
00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:24,040
This is my factory,
I'm not going anywhere.

707
00:39:24,120 --> 00:39:27,520
Foreman Miranda Cleaves! Marvellous.
Beware of imitations.

708
00:39:27,720 --> 00:39:29,880
Clear off out of here, the lot of you.

709
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:35,080
(SNARLING CONTINUES)

710
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:36,880
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

711
00:39:36,960 --> 00:39:39,560
-This will dissolve her.
-And us, too.

712
00:39:42,240 --> 00:39:44,720
-There may be a way back from this.
-From being vaporised? How?

713
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:47,320
Don't know. Let's find out, eh?

714
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:52,440
Geronimo.

715
00:40:03,600 --> 00:40:05,200
Uh, the energy from the Tardis

716
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:08,440
will stabilise the Gangers for good.
They're people now.

717
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,920
And what happens to me?

718
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:14,120
Um...I still have this.

719
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:16,400
Ah! That's not a problem,
I have something for that.

720
00:40:16,480 --> 00:40:20,880
It's small and red
and it tastes like burnt onions.

721
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:24,080
Ha! But it'll get rid of
your blood clot.

722
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:32,480
Happy endings.

723
00:40:38,280 --> 00:40:41,200
JIMMY: Hey! Hello, bud.

724
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:43,440
-Hey!
-Daddy, you're back.

725
00:40:43,640 --> 00:40:46,800
Hello, my boy. How are you doing?

726
00:40:58,480 --> 00:41:00,120
You really want us to do this?

727
00:41:00,640 --> 00:41:03,720
Your company's telling telling the world
that the situation is over.

728
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:07,720
You need to get in there and tell them
that the situation has only just begun.

729
00:41:08,400 --> 00:41:10,440
Make them understand what
they're doing to the Flesh.

730
00:41:10,520 --> 00:41:12,080
Make them stop.

731
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:15,960
Dicken, remember, people are good,
in their bones, truly good.

732
00:41:16,040 --> 00:41:19,200
-Don't hate them, will you?
-How can I hate them?

733
00:41:19,680 --> 00:41:21,120
I'm one of them now.

734
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:24,440
Yeah. And just remember, people died,
don't let that be in vain.

735
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:26,720
Make what you say in that room count.

736
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:29,520
Ready?

737
00:41:36,520 --> 00:41:38,080
Side by side.

738
00:41:38,640 --> 00:41:40,280
You got it, boss.

739
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:46,760
(PEOPLE CLAMOURING)

740
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:50,520
You okay?

741
00:41:51,680 --> 00:41:53,000
I said breathe, Pond.

742
00:41:53,080 --> 00:41:54,400
Remember? Well, breathe.

743
00:41:55,080 --> 00:41:56,520
-Why?
-Breathe.

744
00:41:56,640 --> 00:41:57,720
-Oh!
-Good.

745
00:41:58,560 --> 00:41:59,680
Whoa! Whoa.

746
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:01,320
What's wrong with her?

747
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:03,680
Get her into the Tardis.

748
00:42:03,840 --> 00:42:05,120
(GROANING)

749
00:42:14,120 --> 00:42:16,960
Doctor, what is happening to her?

750
00:42:17,040 --> 00:42:18,600
Contractions.

751
00:42:18,680 --> 00:42:20,880
-Contractions?
-She's going into lab our.

752
00:42:21,120 --> 00:42:24,880
Did he say...
No, no, of course he didn't.

753
00:42:24,960 --> 00:42:27,280
Rory, um, I don't like this.

754
00:42:27,360 --> 00:42:28,360
Ow!

755
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:30,480
You're going to have to start explaining
some of this to me, Doctor!

756
00:42:30,560 --> 00:42:32,080
What, the birds and the bees?
She's having a baby.

757
00:42:32,160 --> 00:42:33,600
I needed to see the Flesh
in its early days,

758
00:42:33,680 --> 00:42:34,680
that's why I scanned it.

759
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:35,800
That's why we were there
in the first place.

760
00:42:35,880 --> 00:42:37,720
I was going to drop you off
for fish and chips first

761
00:42:37,800 --> 00:42:41,480
but things happened,
and there was stuff and shenanigans.

762
00:42:41,800 --> 00:42:44,720
Beautiful word, shenanigans.

763
00:42:44,800 --> 00:42:46,800
-It hurts.
-You'll be okay.

764
00:42:46,880 --> 00:42:47,920
Breathe.

765
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:50,560
I needed enough information
to block the signal to the Flesh.

766
00:42:51,200 --> 00:42:52,200
What signal?

767
00:42:52,840 --> 00:42:54,160
The signal to you.

768
00:42:55,360 --> 00:42:57,320
Doctor, Doctor...

769
00:42:58,840 --> 00:43:00,520
Stand away from her, Rory.

770
00:43:01,280 --> 00:43:03,640
Why? No! And why?

771
00:43:03,720 --> 00:43:05,640
Given what we've learned,
I'll be as humane as I can.

772
00:43:05,720 --> 00:43:08,920
But I need to do this
and you need to stand away!

773
00:43:25,400 --> 00:43:26,920
No...

774
00:43:34,080 --> 00:43:35,880
Doctor, I am frightened.

775
00:43:36,640 --> 00:43:38,560
I'm properly, properly scared.

776
00:43:38,640 --> 00:43:42,080
Don't be. Hold on.
We're coming for you, I swear.

777
00:43:42,160 --> 00:43:45,320
And whatever happens, however hard,
however far, we will find you.

778
00:43:45,400 --> 00:43:47,000
I'm right here.

779
00:43:48,080 --> 00:43:53,680
No, you're not. You haven't been here
for a long, long time.

780
00:43:56,480 --> 00:43:57,480
Oh, no.

781
00:43:57,720 --> 00:43:58,760
(BLEEPING)

782
00:44:01,080 --> 00:44:02,160
(GASPS)

783
00:44:06,000 --> 00:44:07,840
(WHIMPERING)

784
00:44:08,240 --> 00:44:11,880
Well, dear,
you're ready to pop, aren't you?

785
00:44:12,240 --> 00:44:14,160
Little one's on its way.

786
00:44:16,360 --> 00:44:17,720
(WHIMPERING)

787
00:44:22,120 --> 00:44:23,760
Here it comes!

788
00:44:25,080 --> 00:44:29,240
Push.

789
00:44:31,800 --> 00:44:33,080
(SCREAMS)

